			<div class="comment-content">
									
				<p>I don&#8217;t know.  I&#8217;ve heard this argument before on the lamestream news.  Derivatives expire, and are mostly used for insurance to hedge.  Yes, you can loose all your money overnight when they do expire, but banks don&#8217;t (generally) use them to gamble as far as I know.  I agree there are humongous problems with the whole system, though, between fiat money and fractional reserve banking.  I&#8217;m certain the system will collapse soon, but not because of derivatives.</p>
